"title": "7785: shepherd, as occupation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7785",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The occupation of a shepherd was both humble and honourable. In the marginal hill country of Palestine it was particularly demanding.</p>\n<h2>A shepherd as a keeper of flocks of animals</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:32\">GEN 46:32</a> <em>The Hebrew word refers to a keeper of goats and cattle as well as sheep.</em></p>\n<h2>The tasks of a shepherd</h2>\n<h3>Tending, feeding and watering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:2\">PSA 23:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:3\">GEN 29:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:19-Gen26:22\">GEN 26:19–26:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:5\">EXO 22:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:15\">LUK 13:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:15-John21:17\">JHN 21:15–21:17</a></p>\n<h3>Keeping and protecting</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:10\">JER 31:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:2\">GEN 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:4\">PSA 23:4</a> <em>The rod is a crook (for extracting sheep from difficulty) and the staff a club (for warding off wild animals)</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:34-1Sam17:37\">1SA 17:34–17:37</a></p>\n<h3>Leading, not driving, sheep</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:3-John10:4\">JHN 10:3–10:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:1\">EXO 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:2\">PSA 23:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:20\">PSA 77:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:11\">ISA 40:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:6\">JER 50:6</a></p>\n<h3>Gathering animals together</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:3\">JHN 10:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:4\">PSA 147:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:26\">ISA 40:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:32\">MAT 25:32</a></p>\n<h2>The shepherd's routine</h2>\n<h3>The search for pasture</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:17\">GEN 37:17</a></p>\n<h3>The midday rest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:7\">SNG 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>The night-watch</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:8\">LUK 2:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer43:12\">JER 43:12</a></p>\n<h3>Shearing, an annual festival</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:7-1Sam25:8\">1SA 25:7–25:8</a></p>\n<h3>The use of pens and folds</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:9\">PSA 50:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:17\">HAB 3:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:1\">JHN 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:16\">JHN 10:16</a></p>\n<h3>Breeding</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:40\">GEN 30:40</a></p>\n<h3>Rearing</h3>\n<p>Rebekah's ruse depended on a method used to get a ewe to accept an alien lamb:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:16\">GEN 27:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:27\">GEN 27:27</a></p>\n<h2>The problems faced by shepherds</h2>\n<h3>Drought and dry winds</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:4\">JER 12:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:3\">HOS 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:15\">HOS 13:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:17-Joel1:20\">JOL 1:17–1:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:2\">AMO 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>With animals and thieves</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:34-1Sam17:37\">1SA 17:34–17:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:15\">1SA 25:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:1\">JHN 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:12\">JHN 10:12</a></p>\n<h2>Shepherds as employers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:3\">JOB 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:2\">1SA 25:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:4\">2KI 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:1\">AMO 1:1</a></p>\n<h2>Shepherds as employees</h2>\n<h3>The status of a shepherd</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:11\">1SA 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:28\">1SA 17:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:8\">LUK 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>The responsibilities of a shepherd</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:39\">GEN 31:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:12\">AMO 3:12</a> <em>A shepherd who lost an animal to wild beasts had to produce evidence</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:12\">MAT 18:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:4\">LUK 15:4</a></p>",
